    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "**Description of the problem**\r\n\r\n**Full script that generated the error**\r\n\r\n```\r\ngmt begin map\r\n\t  gmt subplot begin 2x2 -Ff5i/3i -M0.5c/0c\r\n\t\t    gmt subplot set 0\r\n\t\t    gmt grdimage @earth_relief_01d -JQ180/? -Rg -Ba60g60 -BWseN\r\n\t\t    gmt subplot set 1\r\n\t\t    gmt grdimage @earth_relief_01d -JQ180/? -Rg -Ba60g60 -BWseN\r\n\t\t    gmt subplot set 2\r\n\t\t    gmt grdimage @earth_relief_01d -JQ180/? -Rg -Ba60g60 -BWseN\r\n\t\t    gmt subplot set 3\r\n\t\t    gmt colorbar -Dx0.4i/0.8i+w1i/0.1i+h+jTL -Crelief -Bxaf\r\n\t  gmt subplot end\r\ngmt end show\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Actual outcome**\r\n\r\n![map](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3974108/131602001-dca60006-7893-4d12-8239-36cadb6682e5.png)\r\n\r\nIf I remove `-Bxaf` in the `colorbar` command, the output figure looks correct.\r\n\r\n**System information**\r\n\r\n* Operating system: macOS\r\n* GMT version (`gmt --version`): 6.3.0_469d64e-dirty_2021.08.28\r\n",
