        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I will label this as user error.  There is no **-R -J** settings for that panel since there is no common **-R -J** settings for the entire subplot, just individual panels.  So when we get to that last panel, we are in the dark.  The **-B** option requires some context here that is not present.  If you move **-Rg** to the subplot begin command then all is well - or if you add -R -J to the last panel.  It works without **-Bxaf** since without **-B** **colorbar** will do its own thing based on its dimension (not **-R -J**).  The **-B** requires **-R -J** to be active.\r\n",
